Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Sambal Teriyaki Chicken Stir-Fry in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Jasmine Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. While you wait, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion shallot{1}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

== Chicken Stir-Fry ==

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British chicken breast{390%g}(diced) and shallot to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and halved).

Once the rice is cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

When the chicken is cooked, add the garlic and green beans to the frying pan.

Stir-fry until the green beans are just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir the @teriyaki sauce{75%g}, @sambal paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @water{50%ml}(for the sauce) and half the @black sesame seeds{5%g} into the pan.

Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Taste and season if needed.

Add a splash more @water{} if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sambal teriyaki chicken stir-fry.

Finish by scattering over the remaining sesame seeds. Enjoy!